    {
        "content": "<p>Also from the other thread:</p>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"125254\">kennytm</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/242791-t-infra/topic/typing.20indicators/near/202575405\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://zulip.readthedocs.io/en/latest/subsystems/typing-indicators.html\">https://zulip.readthedocs.io/en/latest/subsystems/typing-indicators.html</a></p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Right now typing indicators are only used in “Private Messages” views. <span aria-label=\"thinking\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f914\" role=\"img\" title=\"thinking\">:thinking:</span></p>\n</blockquote>\n</blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"125254\">kennytm</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/242791-t-infra/topic/typing.20indicators/near/202575609\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The most likely big change to typing indicators is that we will add them for stream conversations. This will require some thought for large streams, in terms of both usability and performance.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>so a known issue but won't be implemented in the short term</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 202582612,
        "sender_full_name": "Jake Goulding",
        "timestamp": 1593617122
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So I guess take this as a handful of <span aria-label=\"+1\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"+1\">:+1:</span> to the feature request.</p>",
